body:
In regressions of cases from the SystemVerilog LRM, legal case on 1800-2012 page 161 (or 1800-2023 page 209) errors out:

%Error: Class 'ExtClass' implements 'IntfClass' but is missing implementation for 'funcBase'
    | class ExtClass extends BaseClass implements IntfClass;
    | ^~~~~
        ... Location of interface class's function
    |   pure virtual function bit funcBase();
    |                             ^~~~~~~~

**Code:**
```
interface class IntfClass;
  pure virtual function bit funcBase();
  pure virtual function bit funcExt();
endclass

class BaseClass;
  virtual function bit funcBase();
    return (1);
  endfunction
endclass

class ExtClass extends BaseClass implements IntfClass;
  virtual function bit funcExt();
    return (0);
  endfunction
endclass
```

**Version:**
5.044

**Environment:**
Centos 7.9，GCC 11.5

